<div class="colWorkFurther">
	<p><span class="quoteBlock"><span class="quoteOpen">"</span>Phonetics. The voiceless plosive sound made when air is released after a complete closure of the glottis. In some accents of the English, the glottal stop is heard as an allophonic variant of /t/ at the end of syllables."</span></p>
	<p><span class="quoteByline">&mdash; The Oxford Dictionary of English Grammar.</span></p>
	<p>I'm from the South East and I speak Estuary English (EE). I realsied there's a glottal stop within the word glottal. This was such a thrilling discovery that I made a poster.</p>
